interdroid.swan.swansong

Interface Parseable<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type implementing the interface
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Expression, ParseableEnum<E>, TriStateExpression, ValueExpression
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BinaryLogicOperator, Comparator, ComparisonExpression, ConstantValueExpression, HistoryReductionMode, LogicExpression, MathOperator, MathValueExpression, SensorValueExpression, UnaryLogicOperator

    public interface Parseable<E>
    An interface marking an object as convertible to and from a string form. Implementing classes must ensure that all object state is persisted in the string version of the object. Implementing classes must also include a static method: public E parse(String parseable);
    Author:
    nick <palmer@cs.vu.nl>
